\begin_layout Exercise
Assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is finite, prove that the preferences 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq\subseteq X\times X$
\end_inset

 defined above, have a utility representation, i.e., there is a utility function
 
\begin_inset Formula $u:X\to\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 such that for any 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b\in X$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $a\succeq b\implies u(a)\geq u(b)$
\end_inset

.
 
